Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.74,0:00:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain rises on a mysterious new era...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.68,0:00:05.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Monday 7:00 reasoning show.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.51,0:00:07.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something terrible happens while searching for the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.28,0:00:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What will happen to the kidnapped Haibara and Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.98,0:00:11.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.56,0:00:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.48,0:00:15.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:56.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At the Shouin shrine in Tokyo, we rescued Kobayakawa\NKimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} when she was attacked by a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.84,0:01:58.59,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kobayakawa Kimiko (21)\NCollage Student
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.52,0:02:02.66,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,In order to search for "A treasure that could buy the country"\Nthat her deceased grandfather was said to possess...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.72,0:02:05.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We went to Tsuwano, where Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s family home was located.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:12.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,On the way, at Shin-Tamaguchi station, we ran into\NKimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s friend, Kawaguchi Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.23,0:02:13.40,CharCard2,,0,0,0,,Kawaguchi Shigeru (21)\NKimiko's Friend
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.11,0:02:16.70,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,However, Haibara and I noticed that he was using a false name.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.04,0:02:23.78,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,At Tsuwano, we discovered a new riddle and an old map of the town of Hagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.92,0:02:26.73,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,As well as a picture of a cat drawn in the diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.74,0:02:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When, in a search for clues, we went to visit Hagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.58,0:02:35.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I witnessed Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} meeting up with\Nthe man who had attacked Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.29,0:02:38.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, in the end, those mysterious men...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.93,0:02:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What horrible people.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.26,0:02:52.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.39,0:02:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"What should we do?" Of course, we should call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.39,0:02:58.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, that's right. Didn't someone already call for the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.15,0:03:00.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The voice from that time...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.61,0:03:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer! Hurry, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.90,0:03:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kawaguchi Shigeru, I'm a pal of Kimiko's.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is was definitely him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.95,0:03:14.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's from the young mistress's cellphone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.20,0:03:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put it on speaker!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.62,0:03:16.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.75,0:03:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just press this one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.71,0:03:20.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.17,0:03:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We have the woman and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.17,0:03:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Find that treasure as quickly as you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.75,0:03:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you delay, the three of them will...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.13,0:03:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know what.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.17,0:03:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.38,0:03:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't inform the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.72,0:03:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll contact you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.39,0:03:36.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello? Young mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.81,0:03:38.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.15,0:03:42.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should notify the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.41,0:03:51.37,CharCard3,,0,0,0,,{\fad(210,210)}Kikkawa Tsuneo (60)\N{\fs11}Kobayaka Family Employee
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.08,0:03:46.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't! What if we do that,\Nand by some chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.48,0:03:50.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if we obey the culprit, there's\Nno guarantee they'll be rescued.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.95,0:03:52.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.41,0:03:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.74,0:03:58.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} managed to drop this before they grabbed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.29,0:04:00.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.75,0:04:04.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.09,0:04:07.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This picture of a cat and the map of Hagi...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.84,0:04:10.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we turn the map over and put it on top...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.93,0:04:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're the same shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.39,0:04:14.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.85,0:04:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This picture of a cat represents the layout of Hagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.22,0:04:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And "Reflect the castle in the eye of the cat" means...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.10,0:04:25.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Line up the castle on the map exactly with the eye of the cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.19,0:04:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the place corresponding to the\Nhole in the picture of the cat is revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.64,0:04:32.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.24,0:04:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we go there...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.40,0:04:37.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should be able to solve the other part\Nof the code, "Look under the mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.91,0:04:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, I've alerted the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.71,0:04:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.00,0:04:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is the place that corresponds\Nto this hole in the picture of the cat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.09,0:04:47.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look here!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.76,0:04:50.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Um, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.38,0:04:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Enseiji temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.93,0:04:54.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right! Let's go to the Enseiji temple!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.43,0:04:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time to spare.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.06,0:04:59.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"November 30th.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.48,0:05:03.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Only by the twilight will the true treasure be illuminated."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.98,0:05:07.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This evening is the time limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.98,0:05:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can unfasten them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.65,0:05:14.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Luckily, no matter no much noise you\Nmake here, it won't do you any good.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.91,0:05:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So act mature and keep quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:28.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He might say act mature and keep quiet, but\Nwe're not children who would try and act mature.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.21,0:05:30.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.71,0:05:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He'll be sorry he underestimated us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.10,0:05:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.10,0:05:38.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank goodness. You can hear me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.06,0:05:41.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.35,0:05:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is everyone all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.39,0:05:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did they do anything horrible to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.14,0:05:46.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're all OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right now we're in some basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.19,0:05:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you hiding there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.36,0:05:50.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.90,0:05:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.86,0:05:52.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's happening!?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.99,0:05:54.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.61,0:05:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanna get hurt!?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.58,0:06:02.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.66,0:06:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.96,0:06:08.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The police are on the job, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:10.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.72,0:06:14.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is the Enseiji temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.62,0:06:18.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Itou Hirobumi, Takasugi Shinsaku, and the others studied here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.39,0:06:20.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Look under the mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.64,0:06:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.02,0:06:25.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a huge Tengu!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.77,0:06:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.48,0:06:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.86,0:06:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.36,0:06:35.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mice!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's been decorated with all 12 of the Chinese zodiac signs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:39.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.24,0:06:42.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is what "Below the mouse" meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.08,0:06:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is there anything underneath it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.00,0:06:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:50.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, it was something her grandpa who loved puns came up with.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.54,0:06:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it might not mean mouse exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In English, it's "mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.59,0:06:56.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.26,0:06:59.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Mouse" (mausu) is pronounced like "mouth."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.93,0:07:03.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the treasure is somewhere in this mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.10,0:07:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's was below the mouth...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.73,0:07:07.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this be it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.23,0:07:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.77,0:07:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could be this too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.45,0:07:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the largest stone lantern in the prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.95,0:07:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's particularly interesting is that some of the\Nstones supporting the lantern can be moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.29,0:07:28.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.00,0:07:32.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.00,0:07:33.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, that's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.92,0:07:36.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did you know it would be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:40.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That opening in the lantern is called the "fire mouth" (hi guchi).
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.68,0:07:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.97,0:07:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is "below the mouth" too then, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:46.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? What is it this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.10,0:07:48.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.27,0:07:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.98,0:07:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another code?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.98,0:07:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.23,0:07:56.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think the same thing was in the diary.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.28,0:07:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.24,0:08:00.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.82,0:08:02.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It matches the place where the page was torn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.45,0:08:07.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the picture spanning these two pages is the next riddle?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.25,0:08:11.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You must construct a map from the cave where the kappa dwell."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.29,0:08:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if it says, "The cave where the kappa dwell,"\Nthen there's only one place like that in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.92,0:08:17.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are kappa there!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.97,0:08:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akiyoshi Cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:24.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you know where the treasure is?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.64,0:08:26.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are those three people safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.22,0:08:29.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your next destination?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.02,0:08:31.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, you let us hear those three's voices!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.19,0:08:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would you like to be unable to hear their voices for good?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.15,0:08:41.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's Akiyoshi cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.57,0:08:45.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.99,0:08:46.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:52.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I've heard it said that the Akiyoshi cave is\Nthe largest limestone cave in the Orient.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's close to sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.34,0:08:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.47,0:09:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"You must construct a map from the cave."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:09.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden somewhere in here the Akiyoshi\Ncave must be a hint about making a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.90,0:09:12.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This place is called Aotenjou (blue ceiling)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.50,0:09:17.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The light from outside is reflected off\Nthe water, coloring the ceiling blue.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:18.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What about here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.89,0:09:21.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The sign says "Nagabuchi" (long abyss).
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.86,0:09:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One hundred plates?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.86,0:09:25.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They really do look like plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.16,0:09:28.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Limestone caves are marvelous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.66,0:09:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyakumaizara, Nagabuchi, Aotenjou.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.54,0:09:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hyaku?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.04,0:09:37.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.63,0:09:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you figure something out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.25,0:09:40.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.22,0:09:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I rip this here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.84,0:09:47.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.72,0:09:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.43,0:09:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look closely at each of the papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:53.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a character in the upper left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.56,0:09:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.60,0:09:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are the first characters of the names of\Nthe famous places here in Akiyoshi cave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.32,0:10:01.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Ao" is the "Ao" from "Aotenjou."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.73,0:10:03.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Naga" is from "Nagabuchi."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.78,0:10:06.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This one is for the Hyakumaizara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.16,0:10:08.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rest are the same, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.37,0:10:11.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.12,0:10:14.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After this comes Donaifuji (Mt Fuji Inside the Cave).
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.46,0:10:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kabochaiwa (Pumpkin Rock).
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.62,0:10:16.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oomatsutake (Giant Matsutake Mushroom).
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Subogaki (The Mother of Persimmons).
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.13,0:10:19.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Chirimeniwa (Crepe Paper Rock).
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:22.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are the famous places in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.38,0:10:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that means we need to line up these cut-up pieces of\Npaper in the same order, starting from the entrance...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.26,0:10:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we do that, what do we get?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.64,0:10:32.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.39,0:10:34.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't this a map of a cave?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.39,0:10:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this X mark! That's where the treasure is, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.48,0:10:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint is this sentence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.23,0:10:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So if we read it in order it says, "Wa inori..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.65,0:10:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's read from the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.57,0:10:48.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:11:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kuroka radetefu tagonori yuuki tsunei wanokuchi sakihika rinoiwa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.00,0:11:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come out of the black, a pair of dragons.\Nkuro kara dete, futago no ryuu
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.05,0:11:07.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The snout of the Fox Rock, the Light Rock.\Nkitsune iwa no kuchisaki, hikari no iwa
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.76,0:11:10.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it says "Come out of the black"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.10,0:11:13.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Kurotani (Black Valley) exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.48,0:11:13.90,title01,,0,0,0,,{\blur0.5\fad(710,0)}AKIYOSHI CAVE KUROTANI EXIT
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.22,0:11:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Come out of the black" meant come out of the Black Valley exit, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.94,0:11:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the "pair of dragons".
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.40,0:11:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.73,0:11:23.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.03,0:11:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there a place in this area where there are two waterfalls in a row?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.82,0:11:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two waterfalls?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.95,0:11:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, if I remember right, there's a place\Nlike that halfway up the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.78,0:11:35.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those are the pair of dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.08,0:11:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, somewhere near there is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.83,0:11:39.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where the Fox Rock is!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.12,0:11:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.71,0:11:42.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.71,0:11:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could I borrow your cellphone for a moment?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sure, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.13,0:11:50.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who would you be calling at a time like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.64,0:11:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.47,0:11:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry about that, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:57.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.46,0:12:06.59,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The pair of dragons.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.53,0:12:08.28,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.65,0:12:13.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, we're supposed to find a rock in the\Nshape of a fox somewhere near here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing that's shaped like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.45,0:12:19.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder where it could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.30,0:12:29.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the Fox Rock there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.84,0:12:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.39,0:12:33.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That rock?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not shaped like a fox.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.01,0:12:36.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.89,0:12:39.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shadow?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.94,0:12:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, a fox!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the rock didn't make the shape of a fox—the shadow did.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.53,0:12:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, right there just ahead of its mouth. That rock is the Light Rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.12,0:12:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a crevice where someone's affixed a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.95,0:13:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't for the angle of today's evening sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.29,0:13:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light wouldn't be reflected from the crevice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.50,0:13:06.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's move this rock and see what's there!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.51,0:13:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is the treasure inside that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.68,0:13:14.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it has to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.89,0:13:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Genta kun, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.60,0:13:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, we're OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.19,0:13:27.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The path breaks off in two directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.36,0:13:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the right path.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.11,0:13:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right at the next fork too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.61,0:13:32.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another right after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.15,0:13:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then left and another left.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.37,0:13:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right, left, left, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.37,0:13:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right, right, left, left, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:45.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are you shouting?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.67,0:13:48.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I just got excited.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.30,0:13:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is this way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.21,0:13:52.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be there soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.76,0:13:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after the final left...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:58.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.72,0:14:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.47,0:14:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is where the treasure is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.81,0:14:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This light is probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.90,0:14:09.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The light of the moon shining through\Nthe gaps in the rocks on the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.86,0:14:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks so romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.11,0:14:14.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Conan, where's the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.87,0:14:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.79,0:14:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.50,0:14:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.04,0:14:29.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's far enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:32.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Good work.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.38,0:14:33.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you both all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.22,0:14:38.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.51,0:14:41.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hand that over to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.64,0:14:44.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do, we'll return the woman and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.43,0:14:45.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Young mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.64,0:14:46.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do it quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.11,0:14:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.82,0:15:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In such an uncanny location as this, wouldn't it be\Nbest to put an end to any more disgraceful pretenses?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.50,0:15:05.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.21,0:15:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you come out too, Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.47,0:15:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You? What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.93,0:15:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.18,0:15:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, your name isn't really Kawaguchi Shigeru, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.35,0:15:36.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shigeru san's pendant and Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cellphone\Nstrap both have the same kind of initials on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.36,0:15:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s strap says "K.K."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.11,0:15:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, Shigeru{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s pendant says "A.T. "
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.83,0:15:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in addition...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.03,0:15:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though tickets for the steam train were\Ndifficult to get, you were able to obtain them easily.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.96,0:15:53.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could that mean you have a connection\Nto some influential person in the area?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.09,0:15:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that person giving a speech in\Nfront of the station, Takahashi Hisamichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.76,0:16:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was an influential person in the area, announcing\Nhis candidacy for the prefectural assembly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.30,0:16:04.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.85,0:16:08.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think such a splendid father could have a son like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.77,0:16:10.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Atsushi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.23,0:16:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi Hisamichi's son's name was "Atsushi".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.03,0:16:17.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi Atsushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.11,0:16:21.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His initials would be "A.T."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.20,0:16:24.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what I should expect from a great detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.95,0:16:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am Takahashi Atsushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.83,0:16:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been trying to stop the culprits the whole time, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.46,0:16:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the others were taken captive...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.21,0:16:37.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Officer! Hurry, this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.67,0:16:39.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.80,0:16:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like you said, we should have everything out in the open now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:47.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, old man?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.43,0:16:50.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.36,0:16:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.48,0:16:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was the one speaking in front of the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.82,0:17:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Atsushi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} knew his father was\Nafter Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and tried to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.66,0:17:09.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I learned that yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.50,0:17:14.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't care if you need to be a bit rough,\Nbut we absolutely must get that thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.33,0:17:18.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went to Shin-Yamaguchi station so I could tell her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.05,0:17:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would you do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:28.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it obvious? He did it to protect\Nthe person he cares for, Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.39,0:17:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.47,0:17:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the station, Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} seemed to be acting unusually worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.65,0:17:38.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if she was concerned that someone might see her with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.19,0:17:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our relationship...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.19,0:17:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We knew he'd be completely opposed to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.20,0:17:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.62,0:17:49.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That family has kept our area's treasure for themselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think different from the Kobayakawa's.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.08,0:17:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That money should be used for public projects!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.17,0:17:56.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So our area could prosper!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.08,0:17:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.46,0:18:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To go so far as to take children hostage!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.38,0:18:02.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let them go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.76,0:18:05.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, you can go now.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.47,0:18:08.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old man...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:11.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Atsushi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.52,0:18:13.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.27,0:18:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.69,0:18:22.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.86,0:18:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought, it was you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.24,0:18:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one told Takahashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} about the treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.66,0:18:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan took a look at your cellphone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.58,0:18:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he told me there was no record of a call to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.75,0:18:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And here, in this cave...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:39.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason you shouted out the route...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.04,0:18:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to inform Hisamichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the\Nothers who were following us from behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.38,0:18:45.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.01,0:18:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, young mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.93,0:18:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My son had heavy losses in the stock market.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.51,0:18:55.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the company he took out a huge loan from\Nwas a credit company owned by Takahashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.06,0:18:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He told me he would cancel the debt in exchange
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.19,0:19:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm truly...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.98,0:19:03.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Truly sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.28,0:19:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kikkawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.40,0:19:07.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind of joke is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.41,0:19:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.53,0:19:10.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.41,0:19:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the treasure?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:16.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make a fool of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.13,0:19:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A letter written by one of the\Nancestors of the Kobayakawa house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.51,0:19:27.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.34,0:19:32.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I am studying here under Yoshida Shouin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.14,0:19:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"No matter what kind of age may be approaching\Nus, I know a treasure that will never change."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.85,0:19:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The sensei says, 'It is the goals we have in\Nlife that are the fountainhead of all things.'
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.52,0:19:47.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It is having a purpose in one's life that gives rise to everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.28,0:19:53.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"According to his teachings, we students\Nwith the will to make the country better...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.53,0:19:56.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Shall come to see how we can make things different in the real world."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.95,0:20:03.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"From here on, no matter how bitter the winds that may\Nsweep over our world, our greatest assets will be our wills.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.00,0:20:08.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That's what can change the people, and\Ngive them the power to change the country."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.80,0:20:13.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I must rely on my ability with my writing brush in\Norder to communicate this to the generations to come."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.64,0:20:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The power to change the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.65,0:20:23.61,Signs,,0,0,0,,KAERU - BUY
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.98,0:20:23.61,Signs,,0,0,0,,CHANCE
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.10,0:20:20.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't a treasure that could buy (kaeru) the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.10,0:20:23.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a treasure that could change (kaeru) the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.65,0:20:30.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those who are unable to solve my riddle...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.20,0:20:33.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do not meet the requirements to inherit the words of my ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.45,0:20:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.50,0:20:39.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi Hisamichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.58,0:20:43.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What value does your will have?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.75,0:20:46.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I asked you what price it carries.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.34,0:20:50.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If money is enough, is your will for sale?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.09,0:20:54.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A will that can be bought with money...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.51,0:20:56.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.85,0:20:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your will can be bought with money...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.47,0:21:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then it will vanish along with that money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.44,0:21:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.72,0:22:31.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,So this is the Shouka Sonjuku? (Village School\Nunder the Pines, where Yoshida Shouin taught)
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.31,0:22:37.87,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The people behind the Meiji Restoration\Nstudied many different things here.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.07,0:22:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He turned himself in?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.41,0:22:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.70,0:22:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takahashi Hisamichi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did kidnap you and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.37,0:22:50.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it seems Kimiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is denying that it was a kidnapping.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.79,0:22:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How naive of her.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.63,0:22:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, what a waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.47,0:22:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that stamp you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.39,0:23:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the old stamp her grandfather had affixed to the letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.97,0:23:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That stamp had a printing error—the\Ncharacters on it were printed upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.19,0:23:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems it's something that collectors\Nhave paid tens of millions of yen for.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.90,0:23:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kimiko, if you were going to send a letter to the\Nfuture, how much postage would you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.20,0:23:22.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That stamp was his answer to that riddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.20,0:23:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, for his descendants who find that letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.83,0:23:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would provide the funds to try and accomplish\Nwhatever great things they have the will to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.38,0:23:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will definitely get these pasted together.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.67,0:23:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll find the will!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.02,0:23:46.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.64,0:23:48.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that the price of your will?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.81,0:24:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,TASTING
